  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 160°C. Cut the cauliflower into rough florets and add to a large roasting tray. Peel the onions and cut into chunky wedges, then add to the tray along with the whole garlic cloves, still in their skins. Add the spices and olive oil, toss well, then season well. Slide into the oven and bake for 30 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "If batch cooking for the week, let the cauliflower cool then transfer the to a container and store in the fridge until ready to eat. Serve with a drizzle of chilli oil, a scattering of coriander leaves and some sesame seeds."
